The paper deals with interference alignment in a broadcast channel with reconfigurable antennas, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of reconfigurable antennas also involves aspects of networked systems (cs.NI) and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of finite symbol extensions, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.MM) and the achievable degrees of freedom is a performance metric that is often used in optimization and machine learning (cs.LG).
